author: jdcasey
msg: [MASSEMBLY-282] Check for the case where an artifact to be added to the assembly points to the same file that the assembler is meant to create. This happens when appendAssemblyId == false and classifier == null, in cases where the assembly is meant to re-create the standard output artifact from a build, but that standard output artifact should be included in the assembly.
NOTE: I modified the patch to copy the conflicting file to a temporary location, then include it from there, rather than skipping it.
